title: 1891 Limerick Senior Hurling Championship
text:
The 1891 Limerick Senior Hurling Championship was the fifth staging of the <a href="Limerick%20Senior%20Hurling%20Championship">Limerick Senior Hurling Championship</a> since its establishment by the <a href="Limerick%20GAA">Limerick County Board</a> in 1887.
<a href="South%20Liberties%20GAA">South Liberties</a> were the <a href="1890%20Limerick%20Senior%20Hurling%20Championship">defending champions</a>.
<a href="Treaty%20Stones%20GAA">Treaty Stones</a> won the championship after a 2-01 to 0-01 defeat of South Liberties in the final. It was their first championship title.
